supermon-ng (4.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Announcements: upload/TTS, playback, and cron scheduling (modal UI and API).
  * Piper voice catalog: curated picks per region with show-all, on-demand install.
  * Privileged wrappers in user_files/sbin (announce-*.sh) and sudoers entries.
  * Permissions: ANNOUNCEUSER, ANNOUNCEGLOBALUSER, ANNOUNCESCHEDUSER.
  * Recommends: sox, libsox-fmt-mp3, asl3-tts for audio conversion and TTS.
  * postinst: ensure user_files/mp3 and Asterisk sounds/announcements directories.
  * scripts/generate-announcement-voices.py to refresh catalog from Piper voices.json.

 -- Jory A. Pratt <geekypenguin@gmail.com>  Fri, 19 Jun 2026 19:41:40 +0000

supermon-ng (4.2.2-4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * First apt install always overwrites the Apache site from .env (match install.sh).
  * generate_local_allmon: use --if-missing when allmon.ini exists; load .env for paths.
  * postinst: drop duplicate systemd enable/start (debhelper handles units).
  * configure-app-base-path: ensure a single app-base meta tag in index.html.

